{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-25T22:34:19.304Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777156459304_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-012@20260425T183959Za\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-25\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_verify.py`\n- `tests/test_sample_capture_verify.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py`\n- `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly captures a known room sound (synthesized 220Hz sine wave) and confirms that the descriptor record is written to the sample store. The smoke test script `sample_capture_verify.py` successfully validates:\n- Persistence of the WAV file to the correct source directory (`room/`).\n- Insertion of a descriptor row into `index.sqlite`.\n- Correct extraction of context tags (`arc_phase`, `mood`, `presence`).\n- Correct derivation of acoustic tags (`warm`, `sustained`) from the audio signal via FFT-based spectral analysis and transient counting.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is fully complete. A dedicated smoke test tool `sample_capture_verify.py` was added to provide end-to-end verification on the target hardware (cypherclaw). Supporting unit tests in `tests/test_sample_capture_verify.py` cover determinism and descriptor validation logic.\n\n## Consistency\nThe new tools and tests follow established project conventions for sample storage and indexing. The acoustic tag derivation uses the same logic and thresholds as the pre-existing interesting-moment detector, ensuring a unified definition of audio features across the pipeline.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The use of UUIDs for sample IDs and standard path resolution for the capture root is safe. Sensitive information like room presence is handled according to existing context-tagging patterns.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is high quality, modular, and well-documented. The inclusion of a deterministic smoke test provides a reliable way to verify the audio pipeline without requiring manual room recordings during CI/CD or deployment.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No blocking issues found. (Note: Pre-existing `PermissionError` in `tests/test_daemon_fallback.py` due to macOS Seatbelt was observed but is unrelated to this task's scope).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nExcellent work providing a deterministic smoke test for the audio pipeline. This makes verification much more robust than relying on live room recordings. The candidate hardening items regarding `bootstrap_identity` were verified to be already present in the daemon startup flows.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-012@20260425t183959za-verify.md"}}
